IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: Connect2Help(TM) facilitates connections between people who need human services and those who provide them. Individuals and families need to know where to call for assistance in times or difficulty. However, they are often unable to obtain available services quickly and easily due to a lack of knowledge and/or fragmentation of the service delivery system. The purpose of Connect2Help is to help people find their ways to available services.

IRS990.Description: Connect2Help personnel, staffing their 24 hours/day, 7 days/week Call Center, answered 237,729 incoming client phone calls (7.6% more than last year) and provided 367,343 referrals to those clients.

Activity2.Description: Connect2Help(TM) maintains a database of area social service programs. The database included 1708 agencies, providing 5524 programs. Of those 207 agencies and 485 programs were added and 1602 agencies and 6504 programs were updated in fiscal year ending 6/30/2010. In addition to using this data to serve clients calling Connect2Help for assistance, The Rainbow Book(TM) is compiled from this data, published and offered to other area service providers

IRS990ScheduleA.GeneralExplanation: Connect2Help provides information and referral services to callers dialing 2-1-1 in our service coverage area. We also provide information and referral services to callers dialing several incoming specialty phone lines. Several partners operating these specialty phone lines contract with us to provide these services. In conjunction with the compilation and maintenance of our social services database, we contract with community partners to provide data services. Both of these types of related services contracts are included in Section A, line 2.

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: Information & Referral Network is a not-for-profit organization, exempt from income taxes under Section 401(c) of the Internal Revenue Code. However, Connect2help is required to file Form 990 to the IRS by 11/15/2010. An extension has been filed to extend the due date until 2/15/2011.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A draft of Form 990 was made available to all Board Members for comments and suggestions. Form 990 was presented in detail to the Finance Committee of the Board of Directors, which unanimously approved submission of this return. Approval to submit was reported to the full Board and the final version of the return was made available to all Board members.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: Board Chair explains Conflict of Interest policy annually and requests for disclosures are required by the policy.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: A Human Resources subcommittee of the Finance Committee completed a comprehensive review of all human resources policies including a review of salary/benefit packages offered for each job title in the organization during tax year 2009. Job descriptions were matched to comparable job descriptions in local market surveys for all C2H job descriptions. From those surveys appropriate wage ranges were defined and recommended to the subcommittee for approval. The committee approved these recommended ranges for all job titles, including key employees/officers. Board member Meredith Gradle, who also works as a Compensation Consultant for a local corporation, volunteered her expertise in coordinating this review.

GeneralExplanation.ReturnReference: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: All Corporate and governing documents are made available to the Public upon request.
